Siyabonga Langelihle Ngcobo, 21, was found burned in the boot of his car on March 2. Police have said the motive was yet unknown but that they are treating the case as a murder. Activists from the NGO Not in My Name were joined by hundreds of drivers from e-haling services such as Uber and Taxify, who took to the streets of Pretoria on Friday, demanding justice for the young man's death, sayÂ Daily Maverick. 